newsitem.title: USA: US Treasury's 2-yr note yield seen at 5.95 pct.
newsitem.headline: US Treasury's 2-yr note yield seen at 5.95 pct.

text.p: The U.S. Treasury's auction of $18.25 billion in two-year notes on Tuesday is expected to produce a yield near 5.95 percent, dealers said.
Analysts said foreign demand would be a key to the auction's success.
At 1251 EDT/1651 GMT, the two-year notes were quoted at 5.945 percent in when-issued trade.
The bidding deadline for the notes is 1300 EDT/1700 GMT and results are expected around 1345 EDT/1745 GMT.
